itunes:summary:
Ross Patterson and Dan Hollaway are joined by Rob O’Neil, former SEAL Team 6 member and the man who killed Osama bin Laden to discuss why the United States still needs a traditional standing military, using hallucinogens to treat PTSD, the funniest thing that happened during. The bin Laden raid, the Super Bowl, and O’Neil’s upcoming book ‘The Way Forward’.
